In preservative, all dorsal surfaces cream with many small, dark, lavender punctuations and scattered bigger dark flecks (
Fig. 1–2
); venter cream. Bones white in preservative but possibly green in life as in other members of the group. Parietal peritoneum clear, without guanophores in a bib­like fashion; pericardial, hepatic, and visceral peritonea, sclera and testes white (covered by guanophores); gall and urinary bladders clear (
Fig. 4
).
